From: Christian Kohn <chris.kohn@amd.com>
Subject: [PATCH] drm2d: Use ARGB8888 framebuffer format

The zynqmp-dpsub primary plane does not support DRM_FORMAT_XRGB8888
but does support DRM_FORMAT_ARGB8888. These formats are identical in
layout, differing only in that ARGB8888 has a meaningful alpha channel
(which kmscon sets to 0 via memset anyway).

Use ARGB8888 for dumb buffer framebuffers to support drivers that
lack XRGB8888 on the primary plane.

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [zynqmp-dpsub workaround]

AI-Generated: Claude Opus 4.6
Signed-off-by: Christian Kohn <chris.kohn@amd.com>
---
 src/uterm_drm2d_video.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/src/uterm_drm2d_video.c
+++ b/src/uterm_drm2d_video.c
@@ -57,7 +57,7 @@
 	uint32_t pitches[4] = {rb->stride, 0, 0, 0};
 	uint32_t offsets[4] = {0, 0, 0, 0};

-	return drmModeAddFB2(fd, width, height, DRM_FORMAT_XRGB8888, handles, pitches, offsets,
+	return drmModeAddFB2(fd, width, height, DRM_FORMAT_ARGB8888, handles, pitches, offsets,
 			     &rb->id, 0);
 }
